The paper deals with optimization of MIMO transceivers for multimedia streaming in interference networks, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and network optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with network optimization and control, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper focuses on application-level performance metrics for multimedia streaming, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes a dynamic optimization algorithm, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques and algorithms, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
